@dev Get the list of staked tokens of the user
 @param user  user address
@dev totalSupply of coinage
@dev balanceOf of tokenId's coinage
@dev mining end time
@dev get price
@dev current liquidity time of tokenId
@dev current liquidity time of tokenId
@dev expected claimable amount

params.afterTotalSupply: Total amount of coinage after being mined
params.prevTotalSupply: Total amount of coinage before mining

params.afterTotalSupply: Total amount of coinage after being mined
params.prevTotalSupply: Total amount of coinage before mining

returns.balanceOfRayTokenId: balanceOf of tokenId with ray unit
returns.minableAmountRay: minable amount of tokenId with ray unit

claim(uint256).details: The amount mined with the deposited liquidity is claimed and taken.      The amount of mining taken is changed in proportion to the amount of time liquidity       has been provided since recent mining

returns.args: liquidity,  startTime, claimedTime, startBlock, claimedBlock, claimedAmount

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

getRoleMember(bytes32,uint256).details: Returns one of the accounts that have `role`. `index` must be a value between 0 and {getRoleMemberCount}, non-inclusive. Role bearers are not sorted in any particular way, and their ordering may change at any point. WARNING: When using {getRoleMember} and {getRoleMemberCount}, make sure you perform all queries on the same block. See the following https://forum.openzeppelin.com/t/iterating-over-elements-on-enumerableset-in-openzeppelin-contracts/2296[forum post] for more information.

getRoleMemberCount(bytes32).details: Returns the number of accounts that have `role`. Can be used together with {getRoleMember} to enumerate all bearers of a role.

getUserStakedTokenIds(address).details: Get the list of staked tokens of the user

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

infos().details: Give the infomation of this stakeContracts

miningCoinage().details: mining on coinage, Mining conditions :  the sale start time must pass, the stake start time must pass, the vault mining start time (sale start time) passes, the mining interval passes, and the current total amount is not zero,

returns.fee: The fee associated with the pool
returns.feeGrowthInside0LastX128: The fee growth of token0 as of the last action on the individual position
returns.feeGrowthInside1LastX128: The fee growth of token1 as of the last action on the individual position
returns.operator: the address that is approved for spending this token
returns.tickLower: The lower end of the tick range for the position
returns.tickUpper: The higher end of the tick range for the position
returns.token0: The address of the token0 for pool
returns.token1: The address of the token1 for pool
returns.tokensOwed0: The uncollected amount of token0 owed to the position as of the last computation
returns.tokensOwed1: The uncollected amount of token1 owed to the position as of the last computation

returns.feeProtocol: The protocol fee for both tokens of the pool
returns.observationCardinality: The current maximum number of observations stored in the pool,
returns.observationCardinalityNext: The next maximum number of observations, to be updated when the observation.
returns.observationIndex: The index of the last oracle observation that was written,
returns.sqrtPriceX96: The current price of the pool as a sqrt(token1/token0) Q64.96 value
returns.tick: The current tick of the pool
returns.unlocked: Whether the pool is currently locked to reentrancy

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `account`.

resetCoinageTime().details: reset coinage's last mining time variable for tes

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

setPoolAddress(uint256).details: With the given tokenId, information is retrieved from nonfungiblePositionManager,      and the pool address is calculated and set.

params.tickLower: The lower tick of the range
params.tickUpper: The upper tick of the range

returns.secondsInside: The snapshot of seconds per liquidity for the range
returns.secondsPerLiquidityInsideX128: The snapshot of seconds per liquidity for the range
returns.tickCumulativeInside: The snapshot of the tick accumulator for the range

params.deadline: the deadline that valid the owner's signature

withdraw(uint256).details: withdraw the deposited token.      The amount mined with the deposited liquidity is claimed and taken.      The amount of mining taken is changed in proportion to the amount of time liquidity      has been provided since recent mining

userdoc.notice: Uniswap V3 Contract for staking LP and mining TOS
